This paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with automatic speech recognition, which is a subfield of natural language processing. 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper focuses on acoustic modeling for speech recognition, which falls under the domain of sound processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel approach to improve the performance of an A2W recognizer using word embeddings, which is a machine learning technique. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper deals with improving the performance of an end-to-end automatic speech recognition system, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence.
